  "guided": true,
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "No new keys today. The work is rhythm, and prose is where rhythm lives. We will take three plain words and repeat each one at a single, level tempo - the pace good writing keeps when it is going well."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on the home row, thumbs over the space bar, eyes off your fingers. Repeat each word without hurrying. If the tempo wanders, count it out: one, two, three, four."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "metronome",
      "title": "Even hands",
      "text": "I have watched fast hands fall apart on a tight deadline and steady ones sail through. The difference was never speed. It was an even gap between keystrokes. Hold the gap; the speed follows on its own."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "writing writing writing writing writing",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: writing",
      "hint": "Repeat at one tempo: writing - writing - writing. Keep the gaps equal."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "brother brother brother brother",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: brother",
      "hint": "Repeat steadily, no jerks: brother - brother - brother."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "smile smile smile smile",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "Rhythm: smile",
      "hint": "Repeat evenly: smile - smile - smile. Do not speed up at the end."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Let the hand take each word whole, the way you read a familiar name without spelling it. Even repetition is what turns the motion into habit - and habit is what holds the line when the thought is racing ahead of you."
    },
    {
      "type": "pullquote",
      "text": "Loosen your shoulders and your wrists, picture the metronome, and let rhythm set the speed. Calm, even hands finish clean.",
      "by": "Eleanor Hayes, editor"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "All three done? Open the trainer below and take one clean run at the full lesson text. That run saves your progress and unlocks the next lesson."
    }
  ],
